    <dependencies>050, 051, 052</dependencies>
    <completion-notes>
      6 tests authored — 3 happy-path (1 per migrated playbook: documents/emails/events) +
      3 exclusion-path (over-disclosure regression checks). All pass; full integration suite
      63/63 green; full BFF unit suite 7486 pass / 0 fail / 110 pre-existing skips. Build
      0 errors / 1 pre-existing warning. No NuGet adds; no .claude/ writes.

      Orchestrator entry point chosen: direct-executor sequence (not PlaybookOrchestrationService
      with INodeService). Justification: the migrated playbook JSON files live in
      projects/spaarke-daily-update-service/notes/playbooks/ as file-only artifacts (not seeded
      into Dataverse sprk_playbooknode rows), so the production orchestrator's GetNodesAsync
      path would fail. The direct-executor sequence wires the REAL production
      LookupUserMembershipNodeExecutor + QueryDataverseNodeExecutor + CreateNotificationNodeExecutor
      against the REAL production TemplateEngine and dispatches them in topological order —
      mirroring the orchestrator's ExecuteNodeBasedModeAsync behavior. The migration defect
      under test (broken FetchXML + missing membership filter) is exercised end-to-end this way.

      Fixture-shape decisions:
        - In-memory IMembershipResolverService Strict mock seeded per scenario (matter ids).
        - StubDataverseHandler honors fetchXml 'in' filter on regarding attribute so the
          exclusion-path tests correctly produce zero rows when the user has no memberships.
        - Pre-render of FetchXML via TemplateEngine BEFORE dispatching to QueryDataverse-shaped
          executor — needed because QueryDataverseNodeExecutor only does a narrow set of
          well-known-token replacements (timeWindowHours, etc.) and does NOT invoke
          ITemplateEngine.Render on FetchXml. Documented in fixture rationale comments.

      Deferred:
        - Latent finding (NOT addressed here, outside task scope): QueryDataverseNodeExecutor
          does not currently invoke ITemplateEngine.Render on the FetchXML, so the production
          execution of these migrated playbooks would also need pre-render somewhere upstream.
          If P11 UAT (task 110) surfaces this, the fix is either (a) add Render in
          QueryDataverseNodeExecutor.ResolveFetchXmlVariables, or (b) have the orchestrator
          pre-render ConfigJson. Out of scope for the integration-test task.
    </completion-notes>
